    "preGame": "üéôÔ∏è Hello everybody! This is Nok the Corrupter, coming to you live from the nose-bleed heights of Oread's Summit! We are perched atop The High-Pass Pitch, where the air is so thin you‚Äôd think the Guild of the Black Sky was charging for every breath! We're in the thick of the Winners Bracket, and let me tell you, the playoff atmosphere is electric‚Äîor maybe that‚Äôs just the static from the impending blizzards! The Confluence Captains lead this Best of 3 series 1-0, and they‚Äôre looking to close the deal and send the Tamers down to the Losers Bracket where the Haven Lights probably belong! üèîÔ∏è\n\nI just saw Ladew Evelina chugging her customary raw egg‚Äîshell and all‚Äîand she looked like she was ready to headbutt a mountain! On the other side, the Tamers are looking desperate. Saloma Talich is having his teammates punch him in the shoulder with enough force to crack a rib, and Swamy Ahasuerus is dunking her hands in ice water. I suppose if the weather doesn't freeze your fingers off, the well water will! It‚Äôs a beautiful day for a tragedy, folks! ü•ö\n\nSpeaking of tragedies, I think I see a few of the realm's 'heroes' in the VIP box. Is that Nikos Thanae looking 'benevolent' while clutching his coin purse? Or perhaps Sir Garon Ironrock is just here to admire the stonework of the pass! Regardless of the company, the Captains are trying to stay focused. I saw O'Conner Maighdlin speaking only in rhymes earlier; I hope his poetry is as sharp as his hatchet, because he's going to need it to survive the altitude! üß§\n\nThe crowd today is... well, it's sparse compared to those Zmeigorod Snessenger fanatics, but the ones who made the climb are screaming loud enough to trigger an avalanche! The Captains have the momentum, but the Tamers have the home-field advantage of vertigo and sudden blizzards. Will the Captains sweep the series, or will the Tamers claw their way back? Grab your gear and hold onto your souls, because Tuesday Night Trollball is on the air! üì¢",
    "postGame": "üèÜ Holy Mackerel, what a display of high-altitude homicide! The Oread's Summit Tamers have pulled off a miraculous 9-6 victory, evening this series at 1-1! We are going to a Game 3, sports fans! The Confluence Captains came in looking for a sweep, but they ran into a wall of mountain muscle and thin-air desperation. It was a game of two halves and enough injuries to keep a dozen healers like Kant Langill busy until next season! üèüÔ∏è\n\nThe action started with a bang as Dric Trilley decided she didn't like the look of the goal and put the ball through it from Center Field for a 2-point shoot! The Captains answered back quickly with Deach Sharlene‚Äîwho apparently plays better with his boots on the wrong feet‚Äîcharging into the End Zone for a thunderous dunk! It was a back-and-forth affair that saw more leather and blood flying than a butcher's shop in a hurricane! üí•\n\nBut let‚Äôs talk about that first-half massacre! The Tamers' defense turned into a literal meat grinder. Mitran Mariand laid out O'Conner Maighdlin, and before we could even blink, Dric Trilley sent Richia Pazit to the dirt. The injuries started piling up like gold in a money priest‚Äôs vault! Caves Cestar, Ladew Evelina, Belding Chloe, and Carnahan Laud all went down hard. It‚Äôs a wonder anyone was left to hold the ball! Clippard Burr even decided to tackle Stephan Lisk just for the fun of it before the halftime whistle! ü§ï\n\nAfter the break, the Captains tried to regain their footing, but the High-Pass Pitch had other ideas. We saw interceptions flying left and right! Deach Sharlene snagged a wild pass from Kass Fogel, only for Behl Berstine to get laid out immediately after. The violence reached such a fever pitch that the game had to be momentarily halted because one team simply ran out of vertical players! That is the kind of commitment to the sport I love to see‚Äîplaying until you physically cannot stand! üöë\n\nRichia Pazit managed to claw a dunk back for the Captains, but the Tamers were relentless. O'Conner Maighdlin tried to keep the away team in it with a stunning long-distance shoot, but the Tamers' synergy was just too much. Swamy Ahasuerus, despite dropping a few passes earlier, delivered a beautiful ball to Dric Trilley in the End Zone for a massive score that sent the mountain fans into a frenzy! üèîÔ∏è\n\nI have to mention the interference of the elements. Between the Glowstone Glare from the visitors' gear and the dizzying heights, it‚Äôs a miracle anyone could see the goal! Even the legendary Alwyn Wandy got into the scoring act with a 2-point shoot from the Away Field! It was as if the very mountains were pushing the ball into the basket for the home team. The 'heroes' in the stands must have been clutching their pearls at the sheer brutality of it all! üå¨Ô∏è\n\nRichia Pazit tried to mount a late-game comeback with another 2-point shoot from the Home 2-Point zone, but it was like throwing a bucket of water on a forest fire. The Tamers were simply too hungry for that series tie. The Captains looked winded, and who can blame them? Chugging raw eggs is great for the spirit, but it doesn't do much for your lungs when the air is this thin! üç≥\n\nBy the final whistle, the field looked like a battlefield from the Everwar, but with more sportsmanship and slightly less permanence. The Tamers stand tall at 9 points, leaving the Captains at 6. My favorite Ebon Gate Corruptors would have appreciated the way Saloma Talich and Zadoc Wyatan dismantled the Captains' offensive line toward the end. It was a masterclass in physical persuasion! üòà\n\nSo, we head back to the drawing board for Game 3! The Captains have the popularity and the talent, but the Tamers have the mountain's favor and a renewed sense of bloodlust. Will the Guild‚Äôs favorites crumble under the pressure, or will they find their rhythm again? One thing is for sure: the loser of the next game is heading straight to the Losers Bracket, and I‚Äôll be there to laugh at their misfortune! üìâ\n\nFinal score: Oread's Summit Tamers 9, Confluence Captains 6! This series is TIED! I'm Nok the Corrupter, and if you'll excuse me, I need to go see if Imra has any 'dust' left to help me deal with this altitude sickness. Stay brutal, stay bloody, and we'll see you for the tie-breaker! Goodnight, Osterra! üéôÔ∏è‚ú®",
