    "preGame": "Greetings, you ghouls and ghosts! It's a blood-curdlingly beautiful Tuesday night here in the sinking pits of Zmeigorod! We are live at the Serpent's Pass for the do-or-die, winner-takes-all conclusion of this Best of 3 series! üèüÔ∏è The atmosphere is absolutely electric, and not just because of the swamp gas igniting! The fans have turned out in droves for the hometown Snessengers‚Äîhonestly, the popularity of this team is reaching legendary status, probably because there's nothing else to do in the marsh but watch people get clobbered! \n\nThe South Pole Yetis have traveled a long way from their frozen stockades, and they look ready to frost over the competition. I saw Udela Dorkus earlier, giving her quarterstaff a good lick‚Äîthat's a whetstone-flavored ritual that would make the sparkly 'heroes' of the Haven Lights faint with disgust! üèîÔ∏è On the other side, Alded Sanjay of the Snessengers is going around looking every teammate in the eye with a firm nod. It‚Äôs that kind of grit that separates the warriors from the weaklings like Sir Artorias! \n\nWe‚Äôre at the Serpent's Pass, folks, so keep an eye out for rockslides and altitude sickness! This stadium has to be rebuilt every time it sinks into the muck, much like the hopes of the losers tonight! üêä This is the playoffs, the Losers Bracket finale! The loser goes home, and the winner moves on to keep the dream of carnage alive! Grab your raw eggs and mushroom-rubbed elbows, because this is going to be a real humdinger of a finale! üç∫",
    "postGame": "And that's the whistle, folks! A complete and utter shut-out in the swamp! The Zmeigorod Snessengers have defended their sinking home turf with a resounding 4-0 victory over the South Pole Yetis, clinching the series 2-1! üêä What a magnificent display of violence and precision! The hometown crowd is going absolutely wild, and I suspect the local tavern owners are going to have a very profitable, albeit very messy, night ahead of them! \n\nThe action started right away with Alded Sanjay snatching the ball in Center Field, evading a desperate tackle from Ajit Serge. The Snessengers were moving like greased eels in the mud! Northway Orran and Kleinstein MacGregor were orchestrating a beautiful series of passes early on, though Evalyn Pierrepont‚Äôs early shot went wide. It didn't matter, though, because the physical dominance was just beginning! ü¶¥\n\nLet‚Äôs talk about the hits, because that‚Äôs why we‚Äôre all here! Dare Wynnie absolutely leveled Ajit Serge in the Away Field, sending that Yeti straight to the healer‚Äôs tent with an injury that sounded like a dry branch snapping! üí• The crowd erupted! It was the kind of bone-crunching music that makes me wish my boss, Lord Orzalon, was here to enjoy the symphony of pain! \n\nThe Yetis tried to strike back, with Sale Tocci managing to intercept a wild pass from Evalyn Pierrepont and putting the Snessenger star in the dirt with a fierce injury of her own! üß™ It was a back-and-forth carousel of carnage! For a moment, it looked like the Yetis might actually mount a defense as Kleinstein MacGregor leveled Udela Dorkus just before the halftime break. \n\nAfter the half, the Snessengers decided they were done playing with their food! The brutality reached a fever pitch when Gere Cordelie delivered a tackle to Sayers Erdda that had the medical staff scrambling! üî® The 'heroes' like the White Ravens would probably call for a timeout and a lecture on ethics, but here in Zmeigorod, we just call that a Tuesday night highlight reel!\n\nThen came the scores! Northway Orran, after a season of theatrical posing, finally put those muscles to work! She tore through the Yeti defense like a hot knife through butter, sprinting into the End Zone for a thunderous dunk! üèÄ 1-0 Snessengers! The Palisade-dwellers looked frozen in shock, unable to stop the momentum of the marsh! \n\nBut the Snessengers weren't satisfied with a slim lead! Kleinstein MacGregor followed suit shortly after, weaving through the Yetis like a specter in the night. Another dunk, another point! ü•Ö 2-0! The Yetis were starting to look more like 'Not-ies' as they struggled to keep their footing on the sinking field. I haven't seen this much sliding around since Sawyer the rogue tried to escape a circus! \n\nThen came the final nail in the frozen coffin! Arni Griffith, who had been giving the Trollball a heroic backstory all night, decided to give it a happy ending! From all the way out in Center Field, Griffith let fly a magnificent shot that sailed through the uprights for 2 big points! üéØ A 2-point shoot that put the game completely out of reach at 4-0! \n\nI must comment on the sheer popularity of this Zmeigorod squad! The stands were packed with swamp-dwellers and adventurers alike, all roaring for blood and baskets. The Yetis, despite their grit, just couldn't compete with the raw energy of a stadium that is literally trying to swallow the players whole! üå®Ô∏è It‚Äôs a sad day for the southern frontier, but a glorious victory for the Bog Queen‚Äôs favorites! \n\nThe South Pole Yetis are headed to the bottom of the bracket, while the Zmeigorod Snessengers march on! I bet those high-and-mighty Wardens are shaking in their fancy boots seeing this kind of dominant play! üç∫ Final score: Zmeigorod 4, South Pole 0! I'm Nok the Corrupter, reminding you to keep your weapons sharp and your heart corrupted! Goodnight, Osterra! üíÄ",
