    "preGame": "Step right up, ladies and gentlemen, ghouls and ghosts! This is Nok the Corrupter coming to you live from the South Pole Palisade! Holy cow, it is a chilly one down here on the frozen frontier! üèüÔ∏è We are deep in the trenches of the Losers Bracket, folks, and the atmosphere is thicker than the frozen mud on this field! This is Game 2 of our Best of 3 series, and the pressure is higher than a mountain giant's waistline! The Zmeigorod Snessengers are looking to claw their way back after a tough loss in Game 1, while the South Pole Yetis are looking to shut the door and send those swamp-dwellers packing! The fans are out in droves, despite the freezing rain and the occasional wolf pack howling in the distance. I can see the Snessenger faithful have traveled well, probably because anywhere is better than a sinking swamp! üêä\\n\\nLook at the sidelines, folks! Delija Dowling of the Snessengers is chugging a raw egg, shell and all‚Äînow that's a man who knows how to start a morning! On the other side, Udela Dorkus is literally licking a whetstone. I don't know if it helps her game, but it sure makes the 'heroes' of the realm like Sir Artorias look like they're playing a game of tea party! These Yetis are at home in this log stockade, and they are ready to defend their frozen turf with everything they've got! üèîÔ∏è\\n\\nI see the grog is flowing freely in the stands, which is good because you'd need to be half-crocked to enjoy this weather! The Snessengers are known for their high alcohol tolerance, and I expect Evalyn Pierrepont to be playing with a certain... liquid confidence tonight! Can the Snessengers survive the Icy Field and the freezing rain to force a Game 3? Or will the Yetis send them to the abyss? Grab your coats and your cudgels, because we are about to see some playoff carnage! üç∫",
    "postGame": "And that is the final whistle, folks! What a magnificent display of swamp-bred grit in the middle of a frozen wasteland! The Zmeigorod Snessengers have come into the South Pole Palisade and absolutely shut the freezer door on the Yetis with a 3-0 victory! We are tied up, ladies and gentlemen! One game apiece! This series is going the distance, and my black heart couldn't be happier! üêä\\n\\nThe Snessengers came out swinging, literally! Gere Cordelie snagged that Trollball right at the start, and the Snessengers' offense looked as smooth as a greased goblin. Kleinstein MacGregor was tearing up the frozen mud early, showing those Yetis that altitude sickness isn't the only thing that can make you dizzy! It was a masterclass in possession right from the opening tip-off! ü¶¥\\n\\nThe first big blow came from the star of the night, Northway Orran! She didn't just walk it in; she performed those aggressive, theatrical poses right into the End Zone for a thunderous dunk! 1-0 Snessengers! But she wasn't done there, oh no! Moments later, she lined up a shot from Center Field and nailed it! üéØ That's a 2-point shoot, putting the Snessengers up 3-0 before the Yetis even knew what hit them! Talk about a cold start for the home team!\\n\\nBut Trollball isn't just about points, it's about the pain! Duky Orelee decided to remind everyone where they were by absolutely leveling Avaria Revell, sending her straight to the healer! üí• It was a beautiful hit, the kind of bone-crunching music that makes me wish Sir Tanos were here to feel it! The Snessengers gave it right back, though, with Rose Kluge putting Sale Tocci into the dirt just before the halftime whistle! üß™\\n\\nHalftime gave everyone a chance to thaw out their limbs, but the second half was a pure parade of violence! Isborne Krause started things off by injuring Northway Orran‚Äîa huge blow to the Snessengers' star! Then Sayers Erdda and Duky Orelee went on a rampage, taking out Rose Kluge and Kleinstein MacGregor in quick succession! üèîÔ∏è It looked like the Yetis were going to win by attrition, turning the field into a literal graveyard of Snessengers!\\n\\nHowever, Evalyn Pierrepont clearly had enough of the Yeti hospitality! With an alcohol tolerance that would shame a dwarf, Pierrepont went on a tear, injuring Coussoule Bidle and then Jessy Debbie! üî® The 'heroes' like the Haven Lights would probably call this unsportsmanlike, but I call it a Tuesday night! Dare Wynnie joined in the fun, sending Sayers Erdda to the sidelines with a crunch that echoed off the Palisade logs!\\n\\nThe Yetis tried to mount a comeback, with Sayers Erdda attempting passes and Hilaire Guevara taking long shots, but the Snessenger defense was as impenetrable as the Demon Prison! Every time a Yeti tried to run, they were met with a wall of green and brown! Even the howling wolf packs seemed to go quiet in respect of the defensive stand the Snessengers were putting up! üê∫\\n\\nI must say, the drunkenness of the crowd really added to the ambiance! With the Snessengers' high alcohol tolerance, their fans were still standing long after the local Yetis had keeled over from the cold and the keg! Evalyn Pierrepont was playing like a man possessed‚Äîprobably by a very thirsty demon‚Äîand his physical presence was the anchor the Snessengers needed to keep their lead! üç∫\\n\\nIn the end, the South Pole Yetis couldn't find the basket despite the carnage they inflicted! The Snessengers' early 3-point burst was enough to carry them through a scoreless but blood-soaked second half. The popular Snessengers have silenced the Palisade and forced a deciding Game 3! The Bog Queen must be smiling down on her swamp-warriors tonight! üå®Ô∏è\\n\\nSo there you have it, folks! The series is tied 1-1! The Zmeigorod Snessengers have life, and the South Pole Yetis have a lot of bruises to nurse before the finale! This is playoff Trollball at its finest! I'm Nok the Corrupter, and if you aren't bleeding, you isn't trying! Goodnight, you beautiful monsters! üíÄ",
