    "preGame": "Hello Osterra! Step right up and lean in close, because playoff fever is higher than a warlock's ego! Nok the Corrupter here, coming to you live from Fletchings Field for Game 2 of this nail-biting Best of 3! The Zmeigorod Snessengers are on the ropes after dropping Game 1, and let me tell you, the atmosphere is thicker than a swamp-troll's skull! The fans‚Äîbless their deluded hearts‚Äîhave turned out in droves! This place is packed to the rafters with Zmeigorod faithful, all hoping the Bog Queen Valos has blessed their boots today.\\n\\nOn the other side, we've got Oak & Onslaught, looking to close this series out right here on their home turf! I saw Abner Seidel earlier, and those garishly colored undergarments he‚Äôs wearing for luck are bright enough to blind a basilisk! Meanwhile, Evalyn Pierrepont of the Snessengers was seen giving his helmet a final shine with a very confused-looking live snail. If that‚Äôs what passes for strategy in the Grove, it‚Äôs no wonder they‚Äôre down a game!\\n\\nThe druids have been busy too! Fletchings Field is looking absolutely treacherous with trees and gullies shifting around like a drunken adventurer after a night at Yarp's casino. It‚Äôs a beautiful day for a bit of the old ultra-violence, and with the Warden‚Äôs Watch looking on, every hit is going to feel just a bit more official. Will the Snessengers snap back, or will the Wardens' wood-walkers send them packing? Let‚Äôs find out!",
